@@TJvThreadTimer.Priority
Summary
  Determines the thread's scheduling priority relative to other threads in the process.
Description
  Priority indicates the priority used when scheduling the thread. Adjust the priority higher or
  lower as needed.
  Note
  Boosting the thread priority of a CPU intensive operation may "starve" the other threads in the
  application. Only apply priority boosts to threads that spend most of their time waiting for
  external events.

